<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id056a0c62-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s1622"><num value="1622">§ 1622.</num><heading> Foreign landing certificates</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Treasury may by regulations require the production of landing certificates in respect of merchandise exported from the United States, or in respect of residue cargo, in cases in which he deems it necessary for the protection of the revenue, or to comply with international obligations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id056a0c63-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497">June 17, 1930, ch. 497</ref>, title IV, § 622, <ref href="/us/stat/46/759">46 Stat. 759</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/570/tIII/s3126">Pub. L. 99–570, title III, § 3126</ref>, <date date="1986-10-27">Oct. 27, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3207-89">100 Stat. 3207–89</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
